    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sr-(Pentapeptide-104 s-Staphylococcus Simulans Polypeptide-1 Hexapeptide-40) is a single chain recombinant peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the genes from Pentapeptide-104, sr-Staphylococcus Simulans Polypeptide-1, and Hexapeptide-4. The fusion peptide contains 216 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
